<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Fluvial processes rather than fire primarily disturb the alliance. Plants can survive surface fires by sprouting from the rhizomes and by establishing from buried or blown-in seed (Uchytil 1992b). Native Americans regularly burned tule stands to enhance rhizome growth and produce the best stems for basketry and boat making (Anderson 2005).</div>
